title: Neutron Hole States in Zr-89 Via the (P,D) Reaction at 58 MeV.

x4freetext: Neutron Hole States in Zr-89 Via the (P,D) Reaction at
58 MeV.

x4codes.hlp: Universidad de La Plata, Buenos Aires, Argentina

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.43, p.1116 (1991)

x4freetext: Last checking has been done.
The Target Consisted of an Isotopically Enriched Self-
Supporting Zr-90 (96.33%) Metallic Foil with Thickness
Of 5.98 Mg/Cm**2,was Used.
*En-Rsl* an Overall Energy Resolution was Obtained,
Mainly Due to the Energy Straggling in the Target.
.Distorted-Wave Born Approximation Calculations.
Deuteron Energy Spectrum from Zr-90(P,D)Zr-89 Reaction
Recorded at Angle=20 Degree.
.Two Plastic Scintillators,6 and 10 mm Thick.
The Thickness of the First Scintillator was Chosen to
Stop the Tritons,But not the Deuterons.Energy-Loss
Del`Ta E Signals from the Two Scintillators were Used
For Particle Identification.
.Data-Point Reader Uncertainty.
.By CAJAD.
